The paper deals with the problem of computing parity in a noisy communication network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The network consists of randomly placed sensors, which suggests the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the power of transmitters and the connectivity threshold, which are relevant to the category of signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses techniques from decision trees, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
